Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 (if you don't have a toaster).

Drain through a #sieve{}, then place the @chickpeas{1%pack} on #kitchen paper{} and let them dry for ~{5%minutes}.

Peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated or pressed). Juice the @lemon{1}.

Chop the @parsley{10%g}. Trim the @carrot{1}, then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

In a #salad bowl{}, use a #potato masher{} or #fork{} to mash the chickpeas.

Mix in the onion, half the garlic, half the @ground cumin{1%sachet} and half the parsley.

Add @flour{2%tbsp} and @water{1%tbsp} (double both for 4p). The mixture should be a bit wet and sticky. Add another splash of water if necessary.

Season with @salt{1%tsp} and @pepper{to taste} (double both for 4p). Mix together well.

Place in the fridge until cooled.

== Yoghurt Sauce and Salad Dressing ==

In a #bowl{}, combine the @yoghurt{75%g}, remaining garlic, and remaining parsley.

Add lemon juice, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Keep fresh until ready to serve.

Make your salad dressing by mixing @oil{1%tbsp} (double for 4p) with the remaining cumin and lemon juice, salt and pepper —all to taste.

Toss the grated carrot in the dressing.

== Pitas ==

Bake the @pita bread{4} on a #baking tray{} for ~{4-6%minutes} (or toast them in the #toaster{}).

== Falafels ==

Use your hands to form small round balls from the falafel mixture.

Press the balls tightly together and then flatten like a burger patty.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, cook the falafels for ~{3-4%minutes} on each side or until golden brown.

> TIP: Wet your hands when rolling the balls to prevent them from sticking!

== Assembly ==

Gently toss the @salad leaves{80%g} and marinated carrot together.

Pop the falafels into the pita with some of the salad and yoghurt.

Serve the remaining fillings on the side.